<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>My druid vs Wizard 2-3 higher</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack">TheBlack</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:32 p.m. 26/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> My druid vs Wizard 2-3 higher<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1958" TARGET=_self>Druids vs. Wizards</A> (Phazer)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>I had a Wizard root me and try to burn me out the other day. He was a few levels higher than myself, and it looked pretty ugly at first but I survived. Rather than try to attack with spells, I simply healed out of his offensive attack. I was left with about 1/2 bubble at one point due to an interruption or two on my heals, but I healed out. Given that the Wizard was at most 1 level above me at this point, I would of then had the option to melee him, a battle which I would clearly dominate vs a Wizard. Since this particular Wiz was 3 over me I decided it best to beat a hasty retreat to recoup my mana.
<P>Druids are not designed to be magical attack machines. Used properly however they are tough to beat in the low to mid ranges of experience. Still I would not want to face a high level Wizard 1 on 1 as they get some rediculously powerful spells at the upper levels.
<P>&gt; I was trying a few things with a friend earlier. I found that
<BR>&gt; Wizards tend to have more powerful spells, and can indeed kill a
<BR>&gt; druid with very few problems.
<P>&gt; We were both Level 21, and we started off at the same time. We
<BR>&gt; battled about 2-3 times. I did lose all of the duels, but I
<BR>&gt; believe the reason is because I was unable to use Stinging Swarm
<BR>&gt; (DOT spell) This is because Verant believes it is illeagal, and
<BR>&gt; makes the other opponent lose experiance. Just thought I would
<BR>&gt; let you know, that a Wizard can and does have an advantage over
<BR>&gt; a Druid offensive spell-wise. Perhaps I structured my attack
<BR>&gt; method wrong, but I was simply unable to win. Although the
<BR>&gt; opponents health was nearing death, without DOT we are useless
<BR>&gt; to Wizards.
<P>&gt; Just my opinion, and I COULD be wrong.
<BR>&gt; Phazer
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
